## Software Usage Instructions

Setup dependency packages on Raspberry Pi
1. Create a workspace directory
mkdir -p ~/homer_ws/src
2. Navigate into the source directory
cd ~/homer_ws/src
3. Clone the package repository
git clone https://github.com/linzhanguca/homer_bringup.git
4. Return to the workspace root
cd ~/homer_ws
5. Install missing dependencies using rosdep
This ensures all system requirements are met before building
rosdep install -y --from-paths src --ignore-src --rosdistro $ROS_DISTRO
6. Build the workspace using colcon
colcon build
7. Source the workspace to register resources in the current terminal session
source ~/homer_ws/install/local_setup.bash
8. Add the sourcing command to your .bashrc
This ensures the workspace is automatically available in every new terminal
echo "source ~/homer_ws/install/local_setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc

Setup dependency packages on Server computer with Ubuntu
1. Create the workspace directory structure
mkdir -p ~/homer_ws/src
2. Navigate into the source folder
cd ~/homer_ws/src
3. Clone the navigation package repository
git clone https://github.com/linzhanguca/homer_navigation.git
4. Navigate back to the root of the workspace
cd ~/homer_ws
5. Build all packages in the workspace using colcon
colcon build
6. Add the workspace setup to your bash configuration
This ensures the package is found automatically in new terminals
echo "source ~/homer_ws/install/local_setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc
7. Reload your .bashrc to apply changes to the current session
source ~/.bashrc

Launch nodes in rPi and Server to build map
1. On rPi - ros2 launch homer_bringup homer.launch.py
2. On server - ros2 launch homer_navigation create_map.launch.py
3. Control on either platform with teleop_twist_keyboard or gamepad bluetooth link
4. Rviz - locate the serialize map function and name map to the absolute path of the directory to be used for mapping
5. Rebuild packages with - /homer_ws/ - colcon build - source/install/local_setup.bash
6. Once again launch rPi homer.launch.py
7. This time launch - ros2 launch homer_navigation navigation.launch.py - on server computer to begin autonomous navigation

Optional - CLI
1. mkdir -p ~/homer_ws/maps
2. cd ~/homer_ws/maps
3. ros2 run nav2_map_server map_saver_cli -f my_map
